WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.200
[Amit Varma]: Programs like Make in India and Skill India may be very popular in the country today,

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:15.820
[Amit Varma]: but the truth of the matter is that economic growth usually happens in spite of the government

00:00:15.820 --> 00:00:21.320
[Amit Varma]: and not because of it. Society solves its own problems and markets are the mechanism

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:25.520
[Amit Varma]: by which that happens. Back in the day, if you were a young entrepreneur who wanted to

00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:29.600
[Amit Varma]: start a business, you would have to maybe put your own savings into it or try and take

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:34.600
[Amit Varma]: a loan from a bank or convince elders in your community to help you out. There was friction

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:40.560
[Amit Varma]: in all of this. It was hard to reach scale and completely wild ideas that had a 1% chance

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:45.680
[Amit Varma]: of changing the world, but a 99% chance of failing would never get through. But over

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:50.200
[Amit Varma]: the last few decades, we have seen the rise of venture capital and angel investing with

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:54.680
[Amit Varma]: rich people pooling their money to fund new businesses or successful businessmen with

00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:59.960
[Amit Varma]: lived experience, offering their own money and guidance to early stage companies. The

00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:06.040
[Amit Varma]: utility of this is obvious. In a nutshell, it is rational for me to give 10 rupees each

00:01:06.040 --> 00:01:13.160
[Amit Varma]: to 10 companies if one of them makes 110 rupees, even if all the others fail. This makes moonshot

00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:19.200
[Amit Varma]: ideas more likely to get funded and failure does not carry a stigma with it anymore. And

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:23.520
[Amit Varma]: indeed, so many of the giant companies that dominate the world today, like Google and

00:01:23.520 --> 00:01:28.280
[Amit Varma]: Amazon and Facebook, have depended on just this kind of funding model to reach their

00:01:28.280 --> 00:01:33.520
[Amit Varma]: present heights. Of course, many big mistakes have been made by people with money, and some

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:38.720
[Amit Varma]: of SoftBank's multi-billion misadventures come to mind, as do much hyped unicorns that

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:44.200
[Amit Varma]: seem more like a Ponzi scheme than a legit business. But this is the beauty of capitalism.

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:49.600
[Amit Varma]: There is space to make mistakes, and many companies and venture funds will indeed crash

00:01:49.600 --> 00:01:59.200
[Amit Varma]: and fail, just as many won't. And in the end, society will be better off.

